          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Ahijah over the treasures,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " . . . a strange beginning, for hitherto none but Levites have been in question. We should have expected at least “the ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "other",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " Levites.” Further, the name Ahijah is suspicious, because (1) not found among the proper names in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 23:7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "sqq.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; (2) it stands alone, without any reference to a family, such as is made in every other case (see ",
            "children": []
