    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 20-28.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - These verses describe those Levites to whom belonged the care of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "the treasures of the house of God",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "the treasures of things dedicated",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " \"dedicated to maintain the house of the Lord\" (vers. 27, 28). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 20.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - First, the Hebrew text contains no \"of\" in the first word of this verse; and, secondly, no meaning can be obtained cut of the name ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Ahijah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as it is placed here. The Septuagint reading, \"their brethren,\" is exactly what we should expect, and is paralleled by other passages (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Chronicles 29:34",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). This correction of the present text may be safely accepted, viz. ",
        "children": []
